data.title: Niswonger Performing Arts Center
data.meta_description: Brothers Jordan and Seth bring their multi-instrumental talents and captivating songwriting to stages nationwide! Don't miss their latest releases and join them for an unforgettable hometown show.
data.text:
VIP TICKET INCLUDES: Premium Seating, VIP Lanyard, VIP Signed Poster, Early Entry & Crowd Free Shopping, Acoustic Song and M&G with Photo Opp Prior to Show and Artist/Special Guest Q&A

The Dugger brothers (Jordan and Seth) grew up in Greeneville, Tennessee. They continue a tradition of Country music rising from the Great Smoky Mountains that began with artists like Dolly Parton and Kenny Chesney.

Dugger Band tours nationwide and continues to add to their list of performances at notable events and venues. The band has shared the stage with Charlie Daniels, Josh Turner, Craig Morgan, Charlie McCoy, Mandy Barnett, Rodney Atkins, John Rich and Luke Bryan’s band.

Jordan and Seth, who are both songwriters and multi-instrumentalists, made their debut at country radio with the original tune “East Tennessee Son”. They have released five Country albums to date. Their fifth studio album, “Goin’ Places” was released earlier this year! Come join them for an electric show in their hometown!

(This performance is a venue rental and is not included in the 2023-2024 Season.)
